unittitle_ssm: Fire Department of the City of New York Logbooks and Reports
abstract_ssm: Collection of logbooks and reports from the Fire Department of the City of New York. Logbooks from various Engine Companies and Hook and Ladder Companies constitute the majority of the collection. These volumes date from 1870 to 1957, and document the day-to-day workings of the firehouses. Additional volumes, dated 1893-1913, contain Fire Chiefs' records, assignments to duty, and fire alarm signals.
